We select A–D–A NFAs with representative skeletons as studying examples, including the fused (IT-4F), semi-fused (HF-PCIC), and non-fused-cores (PTIC), respectively (Fig. 2a). Their photostabilities are first investigated by recording the UV–vis spectra of neat films under the continuous one-sun-equivalent illumination in ambient conditions (Fig. 2a and Supplementary Figs. 1 and  2). Among them, the photostability of non-fused PTIC is sharply distinct from others. Note that the maximum absorption peaks (λabsmax\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
